---
name: qa-audit
preamble-tier: 3
version: 1.0.0
description: |
  QA methodology auditor. Scans a project's existing test suite and scores it against
  best practices across 5 dimensions: test pyramid balance, test isolation,
  test data strategy, assertion & naming quality, and CI/coverage & reliability.
  Produces a scored audit report (0–100) with concrete, ranked recommendations and
  before/after code examples. Checks include: test naming, AAA structure, shared state,
  sleep/timing, test data, coverage, CI integration, assertion quality (weak vs exact),
  positive/negative test balance, retry/skip/ignore markers, and parallelization safety.

  Consumes qa-methodology/references/ guides generated by /qa-methodology-refine for
  enriched, sourced recommendations. Falls back to built-in methodology knowledge when
  guides are not yet generated.

  Works standalone or as a sub-agent of /qa-team (writes report to $TEMP/qa-audit-report.md).

  Use when asked to:
  - "audit tests", "qa audit", "test quality review", "test methodology review"
  - "check test suite health", "is our testing good?", "improve our tests"
  - "test pyramid analysis", "why are our tests slow / flaky / brittle?"
  - "test coverage gaps", "how should we structure our tests?"
  (qa-agentic-team)
allowed-tools:
  - Bash
  - Read
  - Write
  - Glob
  - Grep
  - AskUserQuestion
---

