## Phase 4 — Score

Score 5 dimensions × 20 points each (100 total):

| Dimension | 0 | 10 | 20 | Signal |
|-----------|---|----|----|--------|
| Pyramid Balance | Inverted or all-e2e (> 50% e2e); no negative-path tests | Off-balance; some negative tests | Unit > 60%, e2e < 20%; positive + negative paths both covered | Inventory + Check 9 |
| Test Isolation | Shared state + no cleanup; parallel-unsafe resources | Some isolation | beforeEach resets + no cross-test deps + parallel-safe | Checks 3 & 11 |
| Test Data | All hardcoded values | Some factories | Factory/fixture ratio > hardcoded ratio | Check 5 |
| Assertion & Naming Quality | > 30% vague names or mostly presence-only assertions | Some descriptive names, some exact-value assertions | < 5% vague names; assertions verify exact values/structure | Checks 1 & 8 |
| CI / Coverage & Reliability | No CI; unexplained skips/retries everywhere | CI runs; some coverage | CI + thresholds + artifacts on failure + no unexplained skips | Checks 4, 6, 7 & 10 |

A score of 50–65 is typical for projects that haven't explicitly focused on test
methodology. Report the score with context, not judgment.

